Afternoon Tea.\n\nCome the cocktail hour, the classics come into prominence (Cosmopolitan, Whisky Sour, Mojito, Side Car etc.), side by side with champagne cocktails and seasonally changed specials, taking inspiration from the fresh, market produce of nearby Borough Market - London''s most famous gastronomic oasis.\n\nA full bar is of course available with soft drinks, a range of Tea Forté teas, hot chocolate and coffees served by specially trained baristas.";s:10:"post_title";s:20:"Quarter Bar & Lounge";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"quarter-bar-lounge";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-08-15 11:46:59";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-08-15 11:46:59";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=460";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:14;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:690;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-07-26 08:35:05";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-07-26 08:35:05";s:12:"post_content";s:697:"Hundreds of exciting, interactive exhibits in one of London’s most beautiful landmark buildings. Highlights include the popular Dinosaurs gallery, Mammals display with the unforgettable model blue whale and the spectacular Central Hall, home to the Museum’s iconic Diplodocus skeleton.\n\nDon’t miss the state-of-the-art Darwin Centre Cocoon where, on a self-guided tour, you can see hundreds of fascinating specimens and look into laboratories where scientists are at work.\n\nThe Museum offers a wide-ranging programme of temporary exhibitions and events, including chances to join experts in the Darwin Centre’s high-tech Attenborough Studio in topical discussions about science and nature.";s:10:"post_title";s:22:"Natural History Museum";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:22:"natural-history-museum";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-07-26 08:35:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-07-26 08:35:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=690";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:15;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:628;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-07-18 11:57:53";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 09:45:01";s:12:"post_content";s:549:"Indulge in the most decadent of all British traditions and enjoy a delightful Afternoon Tea, moments away from the recognised landmarks of Trafalgar Square and Piccadilly Circus. Being Sofitel St James, we put a French touch on our Tea and offer an exceptional showcase of Parisienne pastries.\n\nDiscover our collection of exclusive teas, end the day with a sip of Champagne in the intimate and elegant decor of The Rose Lounge with subtle colours of pink and cream, stunning displays of fragrant roses further enhanced by the gentle sound of a harp.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"The Rose Lounge";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"the-rose-lounge";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-07-18 11:57:53";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 09:45:01";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=628";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";