ban environment, these are movie screenings with altitude.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Since its inception in 2011, Rooftop Film Club has pioneered the outdoor cinema phenomenon in the UK, becoming a staple of the London culture scene. In the years since Rooftop Film Club has grown a sizable and passionate following, selling out over 250 rooftop screenings across five London venues in 2014 alone.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:17:"Rooftop Film Club";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:17:"rooftop-film-club";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-06 14:40:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-11-04 22:21:16";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=931";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:36;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:872;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-04-03 16:57:19";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-30 15:15:11";s:12:"post_content";s:488:"<p style="text-align: justify;">We are a financial services group with millions of UK customers with a presence in nearly every community; we are familiar on the high street and with over 1 million businesses through our portfolio of brands.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our business is focused on retail and commercial financial services. We thrive based on how well we serve our customers; on our relationships within the communities we serve; and on helping Britain prosper.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"Lloyds Bank";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:11:"lloyds-bank";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-03 16:57:19";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-30 15:15:11";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=872";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:37;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:671;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-04-01 14:58:45";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 10:50:58";s:12:"post_content";s:564:"Founded in 1753, the British Museum’s remarkable collection spans over two million years of human history. Enjoy a unique comparison of the treasures of world cultures under one roof, centred around the magnificent Great Court.\n\nWorld-famous objects such as the Rosetta Stone, Parthenon sculptures, and Egyptian mummies are visited by up to six million visitors per year. In addition to the vast permanent collection, the museum’s special exhibitions, displays and events are all designed to advance understanding of the collection and cultures they represent.";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"British Museum";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"british-museum";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-01 14:58:45";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 10:50:58";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=671";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:38;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:622;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-27 11:47:48";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 09:14:57";s:12:"post_content";s:668:"With venues in both Mayfair and Knightsbridge, Mamounia Lounge allows guests to enjoy a truly authentic Arabic drinking and dining experience in the heart of London.\n\nThe restaurants’ Middle Eastern menu features the very best of traditional Lebanese and Moroccan cuisines aswell as a selection of European fusion dishes created by their experienced head chefs, whilst an eclectic cocktail list is served at the bars by expert mixologists.\n\nPerfect for relaxed day-time dining, at night both venues come alive with beautiful belly-dancers, and traditional Middle Eastern musicians, evoking the energetic buzz of Marrakech, for an unforgettable experience every time.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Mamounia Lounge";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"mamounia-lounge";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-27 11:47:48";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 09:14:57";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=622";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:39;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:262;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-25 17:56:21";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-20 14:12:46";s:12:"post_content";s:720:"Bruce Poole and Nigel Platts-Martin opened Chez Bruce in 1995. From the outset, it was their intention to serve the very best food and drink but within a relaxed, informal yet thoroughly professionally orchestrated environment.\nAt Chez Bruce we are not particularly into gadgets and tricks in the kitchen. Home-made charcuterie, slow cooked braises, offal, warm and cold salads, classical desserts and bread-making could be listed as specialities. We also take the cheese board very seriously indeed and it forms an integral part of the restaurant''s day-to-day life.\nThe Directors of the restaurant are fanatical wine-lovers and are very proud of the restaurant''s wine list which truly is one of the very best in the UK.";s:10:"post_title";s:10:"Chez Bruce";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:51:"2-bellevue-road-wandsworth-common-london-chez-bruce";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-25 17:56:21";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-20 14:12:46";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:108:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?job_listing=2-bellevue-road-wandsworth-common-london-chez-bruce";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:40;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:467;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-25 17:22:53";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-22 14:18:15";s:12:"post_content";s:1056:"<h3>Om Magasinet Jkpg</h3>\r\n<div class="textwidget">Co-Working Space med panoramautsikt över Munksjön i centrala Jönköping.</div>\r\n<div class="textwidget"></div>\r\n<div class="textwidget">Vi är en samling individer och företag som tror att bra saker uppstår när olika världar möts på inspirerande platser. Därför skapade vi gemensamt i början av 2014 Magasinet Jkpg som blir en ny mötesplats i Jönköping. Vi håller till i delar av en större fastighet som är belägen på Östra Strandgatan 10, intill Munksjöns strand, med utsikt över Munksjö industriområde där en ny stadsdel växer fram och<span class="text_exposed_show"> intill Spira och Atollenområdet i centrala Jönköping.\r\n\r\nVår förhoppning är att Magasinet Jkpg blir en plats där affärer görs på ett lustfyllt sätt och där oväntade samarbeten uppstår. Vi hoppas också att vi kommer att se ett flöde av människor utifrån och att ni är många där ute som får anledning att besöka oss eller kanske till och med bli en del av vår arbetsplats.</span></div>";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Magasinet JKPG";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:29:"jumeirah-grosvenor-apartments";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-02-17 11:02:33";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-02-17 11:02:33";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:77:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=467";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:41;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:807;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-21 17:58:56";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 13:55:21";s:12:"post_content";s:479:"The Hummingbird Bakery is an American-style bakery founded in 2004 to bring the authentic taste of American home baking to London. The company opened its first branch on Portobello Road in Notting Hill in 2004 and has since launched a further six branches across London in South Kensington, Soho, Spitalfields, Islington and Richmond. It also has a franchise presence in the Middle East with two branches already operating successfully in Dubai and with further launches planned.";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Hummingbird Bakery";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"hummingbird-bakery";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-21 17:58:56";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 13:55:21";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=807";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:42;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:585;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-19 08:57:01";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 08:33:45";s:12:"post_content";s:612:"The Askew Road location harbours the original bakery which is humming nightly to produce fresh, carefully crafted artisan bread, viennoserie, cakes &amp; tarts. Downstairs the kitchen lights up early to prepare tasty sandwiches and a full breakfast and lunch menu from 7am - 3pm daily cooked to order by our chefs.\n\nInside the shop is a range of goodies for your pantry and plenty to choose from our counter selection, sweet and savoury. There are tables large and small, in nooks and at the front window, communal tables &amp; outdoor seating. In short, something for everyone, tailored to your needs every day.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Laveli Bakery";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"laveli-bakery";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-19 08:57:01";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 08:33:45";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=585";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:43;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:739;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-14 08:35:04";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 12:38:35";s:12:"post_content";s:1486:"Liberty was founded in 1875, but the present Marlborough Street site, with its ships’ timbers and leaded windows, was built in the 1920s. The interconnecting jumble of rooms, with the odd fireplace and cushioned window seat, makes for an intimate feel – as if you’ve strayed into a private room in a stately house. It’s not an accident, founder Arthur Lasenby Liberty wanted customers to feel as if they were exploring someone’s home, keeping the shopping galleries small, albeit linked to three rather grand atriums.\n\nAlthough Liberty trades well on its history, it constantly squeezes innovation into its wood-panelled rooms. Alongside one of the best edits for fashion shopping in the world, in 2011 it expanded its men’s floor, adding a huge tailoring and accessories chamber packed full of posh undies. The Paper Room soon followed on the ground floor with micro-floral Liberty print stationery and gifts, and then the Dining Room opened – quirky cookware and gadgetry in a space modelled on the kitchen in Downton Abbey.\n\nFrench publishing powerhouse Assouline opened its Literary Lounge on the ground floor, where you can flick through fashion, art and photography coffee-table books (which are, oddly, the size of coffee tables). The Beauty Hall then doubled in size with ten new brands – their counters manned by an eerily beautiful staff. And five new treatment rooms are set to open.\n\nUnapologetically eccentric and truly innovative, Liberty is a London icon.";s:10:"post_title";s:7:"Liberty";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:7:"liberty";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-14 08:35:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 12:38:35";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=739";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:44;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:526;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-06 17:42:58";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-22 19:17:14";s:12:"post_content";s:763:"<p style="text-align: justify;">The iconic London Palladium is the perfect venue to host the grandest business conferences, presentations, meetings and receptions. This prestigious theatre’s auditorium seats over 2,200 people, while two bars offer spaces to fit smaller business functions. The London Palladium is situated in the heart of London’s West End, a short walk from Oxford Circus.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">From the roster of stars who have played there and many televised performances, it is arguably the most famous theatre in London and the United Kingdom, especially for musical variety shows. The theatre has also hosted the Royal Variety Performance a record 40 times, most recently in 2014.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>";s:10:"post_title";s:17:"Palladium Theater";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:24:"london-palladium-theater";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-06 17:42:58";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-22 19:17:14";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=526";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:45;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:554;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-05 16:57:15";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 07:42:25";s:12:"post_content";s:1012:"Pollen Street Social is a contemporary bistro offering deformalised fine dining in Mayfair. The flagship restaurant of renowned chef Jason Atherton, it houses a restaurant, social bar, dessert bar and private dining room, and holds one Michelin star.\n\nFor birthdays or business, romance or carousing, “flawless” Pollen Street Social is “the perfect restaurant” – whether you’re wearing jeans or a suit. It really is ‘social’ too, so start with a cocktail in the “ever-so-cool” bar, a taster of the invention and attention to detail to come.\n\nMain man Jason Atherton is opening restaurants at breakneck speed, but this is his special project and the focus of his “imaginative yet approachable” cuisine: scallop carpaccio with kohlrabi, pomelo, yuzu jam, black olive and samphire is an austerely simple assembly of bracing flavours, while playful complexity shows in the signature ‘full English breakfast’ – an eggshell filled with slow-cooked egg, tomato purée, bacon and mushrooms.";s:10:"post_title";s:20:"Pollen Street Social";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:20:"pollen-street-social";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-05 16:57:15";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 07:42:25";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=554";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:46;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:596;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-05 10:56:59";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-23 08:35:50";s:12:"post_content";s:1579:"Vox Hotel has 143 rooms, from suites and deluxe rooms with an amazing view over Lake Vättern to affordble doubles.\r\n\r\nThe hotel is open 24 hours, every day, we have working spaces in the lounge and our gym sports a magnificent view. Vox Hotel is located in the city center of Jönköping, near the train station and close to shopping, restaurants and nightlife.\r\n<h3>Conference and meetings</h3>\r\nVox Hotel offers tailored conference packages in cooperation the best meeting venues and restaurants in Jönköping. <a href="http://voxhotel.se/conference-and-meetings/">See all our conference and meeting options</a>.\r\n<h3>Press</h3>\r\nFor inquiries, interviews, press images and related questions, please contact General Manager Alina Jernbom <a href="mailto:alina@voxhotel.se">alina@voxhotel.se</a>. <a href="http://voxhotel.se/press/">Download press images</a>.\r\n<h3>Career</h3>\r\nDreaming of being a part of building a brand new hotel? Join the Vox team, <a href="http://voxhotel.se/jobb/">apply here</a>.\r\n<h3>Contact</h3>\r\nVox Hotel is located at Lantmätargränd 2 in the city of Jönköping, about 600 meters from the train/bus station (Jönköpings Resecentrum), 6 km from Jönköping Airport. Map and directions <a href="http://voxhotel.se/#contact">here</a>. Call us: <a href="tel:+46367700000">+46 (0) 36 770 00 00</a>.\r\n<h3>Business agreements</h3>\r\nWe would love to see you and your company as our guests at Vox Hotel. Become a Vox Member! Please contact <a href="mailto:matilda@voxhotel.se">matilda@voxhotel.se</a> for more information about our business agreements.";s:10:"post_title";s:9:"Vox Hotel";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:10:"z-victoria";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-02-17 10:59:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-02-17 10:59:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:77:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=596";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:47;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:101;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-02-25 08:06:11";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-13 12:41:12";s:12:"post_content";s:531:"Boasting a spectacular spiral staircase clad in Gaucho’s signature cowhide, the restaurant is split over two floors. The impressive ground floor dining area is flooded with light from the soaring arched windows of this beautiful building, while the upstairs gallery is a glittering display of white leather and glass tables.\n\nDuring the week, lawyers and locals have lunch under the sparkling chandeliers. On weekend evenings, a chic crowd settles in to the boutique mezzanine lounge bar: an inviting hideaway after the sun sets.";s:10:"post_title";s:19:"Roast Chancery Lane";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:19:"roast-chancery-lane";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-02-25 08:06:11";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-13 12:41:12";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=101";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:48;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:312;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-02-23 13:41:28";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-21 12:54:16";s:12:"post_content";s:684:"<p style="text-align: justify;">The green, triangle-shaped expanse of leafy land just beyond the Ritz is Green Park. Penned in at two corners by St James''s Park and Hyde Park, it was enclosed by Charles II in 1668 as a hunting ground before opening to the public in 1826.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Every year millions of Londoners and tourists visit The Green Park, the smallest of the capital''s eight Royal Parks.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Comprising just over 40 acres of mature trees and grassland next to Buckingham Palace, the peaceful triangle between Piccadilly and Constitution Hill offers a popular location for picnics and sunbathing in fine weather.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:10:"Green Park";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:10:"green-park";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-02-23 13:41:28";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-21 12:54:16";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=312";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:49;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:520;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-02-20 10:07:52";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-22 18:45:55";s:12:"post_content";s:511:"<p style="text-align: justify;">Greenwich Park hosts the Prime Meridian Line and Royal Observatory as well as being part of the Greenwich Maritime World Heritage Site which is home to The National Maritime Museum and Old Royal Naval College.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The most historic of all Royal Parks, Greenwich Park dates back to Roman times and was enclosed in 1427. From the statue of General Wolfe the park offers imperious views across the River Thames all the way to St. Pauls Cathedral.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Greenwich Park";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"greenwich-park";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-02-20 10:07:52";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-10-22 18:45:55";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_